# Models

Models (`models/User.js`, `Message.js`, `Chat.js`) define **schema and structure only**:

- Fields, types, defaults, indexes
- Schema-level hooks only when purely structural (e.g. `timestamps`)
- `select: false` for sensitive fields (passwords)

## Forbidden in models

- API response shaping
- Authorization decisions
- Multi-document workflows or chat/matching business rules

Keep schemas **minimal**. Application logic belongs in `services/`.

```javascript
// GOOD — schema concern
password: { type: String, required: true, select: false }

// BAD — business rule in model
userSchema.methods.canMessage = function (otherUser) { /* matching logic */ };
```

Move `canMessage`-style logic to `services/`.
